value.0: A young svirfneblin with a grey-blueish skin. His face is skinny, with its excessive skeletal structure very visible. His nose is long and thin, his eyes are large and can be very penetrating if he doesn't feel sleepy.  Long retired from his days with the Mak'a'nor Mining Company, He now runs a small sleepy tavern called The Dormouse.  He can often be found telling tales from his daring days if anyone can keep him awake long enough.

A mighty iron-banded shield hangs upon the wall, the relic of battles long gone.
Made entirely of wood, this handsomely carved seat exudes comfort and one can see why the owner can be found dozing here quite often.
Comfy Chair
Bound in iron and with a heavy lock, this heavy chest was obviously meant to protect something of value.
The smell of mothballs has long since seeped into the wood of this armoire.
The antique drawer pulls are touched by rust and the drawers themselves fit ill within their sockets. It seems the damp air has not been kind to this piece.
Metal studs poke through the woodwork of this ornate chest. Judging by the fine craftsmanship, this strongbox appears to have been intended for public display.
You can almost taste the hearty mead within the cask. It looks to have aged well.
